# Quality Standards

## TypeScript

Use strict TypeScript configuration with proper type definitions.

## Component Structure

Follow consistent component structure with props interface, component
definition, and export.

## Error Handling

Implement proper error boundaries and error handling throughout the application.

## Performance

Optimize for Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS) and use React.memo() when
appropriate.

## Accessibility

Follow WCAG guidelines and use semantic HTML elements.

## Testing

Write unit tests for utilities and integration tests for components.

## Code Comments

Add JSDoc comments for complex functions and components.

## Naming Conventions

Use descriptive, consistent naming for files, components, and functions.
